                },
                "message": "Improve names in fused __pyx_api\n\nSo that they're based on the types of the argument rather than\nthe slightly arbitrary order of the fused arguments. This should\nmean they keep being right if the fused type is expanded.\n\nKeep the old values around for compatibility, and also support\nloading from the old values. I'd intend to remove this in the end\nbut likely not any time soon.\n\nRelated to #7603 (vaguely)",
